        "id": "cn3_palsy",
        "name": "Oculomotor (CN III) Palsy",
        "prevalenceModifier": 0.3,
        "keyFeatures": [
          { "feature": "ptosis", "weight": 5 },
          { "feature": "eye_down_and_out", "weight": 5 },
          { "feature": "limited_adduction_elevation_depression", "weight": 5 },
          { "feature": "pupil_involved_vs_spared", "weight": 5 }
        ],
        "management": "If pupil-involving: EMERGENCY neuroimaging (CT angiogram / MRI to exclude PCOM aneurysm). If microvascular (pupil-sparing): observation, BP/glucose control. Prism glasses for diplopia. Patch if needed. Recovery 3-6 months."
      },
      {
        "id": "cn4_palsy",
        "name": "Trochlear (CN IV) Palsy",
        "prevalenceModifier": 0.2,
        "keyFeatures": [
